Certora CVL multi-mode composition (the gold standard for temporal-via-composition):
```
persistent ghost mathint totalSupplyGhost { init_state axiom totalSupplyGhost == 0; }
hook Sstore _balances[KEY address u] uint256 newBal (uint256 oldBal) {
    totalSupplyGhost = totalSupplyGhost + newBal - oldBal;
}
invariant totalSupplyMatchesSum() totalSupplyGhost == totalSupply();
rule transferPreservesSum(address from, address to, uint amt) {
    mathint pre = totalSupplyGhost;
    transfer(e, to, amt);
    assert totalSupplyGhost == pre;
}
```
Four modes (ghost, hook, invariant, rule) compose to express a counting+temporal property without a dedicated 'counting' or 'temporal' keyword.

Halmos dual-mode prefix (already in production, directly portable):
```solidity
// Stateless: state reset, symbolic args
function check_transferDoesNotMintOrBurn(address to, uint amt) public {
    uint pre = c.totalSupply();
    c.transfer(to, amt);
    assert(c.totalSupply() == pre);
}
// Stateful: bounded sequence of symbolic calls, persistent state
function invariant_totalSupplyEqSumBalances() public view {
    assert(c.totalSupply() == sum_of_balances());
}
```
Mode = function-name prefix. Halmos detects it and dispatches accordingly.

